snippet.textDisplay: Hey guys, if you are looking for another film to review... When I was a kid I was really impressed by Astérix et Obélix Mission Cléopâtre (https://www.imdb.com/title/tt0250223/). Or if there is an emphasis on certain style of effects? Anyways keep up the good work.

I'd really like it if you guys would take a look at Batman Forever...apparently it was one of the first films to use a CGI character as a stunt double. (I'm thinking it's the scene where Batsy takes a dive from a a very tall building.)


Dragonheart: Sean Connery's mouth movements animated for the CGI dragon, supposedly based on Connery's old films (without facial hair, I'm guessing). That would be a good one to look at as well.

snippet.textDisplay:
Hi guys! Absolutely love your videos! I've been wondering if you've ever seen 90s Sci Fi show Babylon 5? Sure the CG is heavily dated but for it's time there was no other show to use CG so extensively. The difference between season 1 and season 4 is night and day!
Also, Patricia Tallman who stared in the show was also one of the lead stunt performers on Star Trek TNG, I'm certain she would be more than happy to provide some insight into how a TV show was able to deliver such great FX and stunts for its day!

All the best guys
snippet.textOriginal:
